SIMPLE: lodging
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lodging
<hw>Lodg"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of one who, or
that which, lodges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place of rest, or of temporary habitation; esp., a
sleeping apartment; -- often in the plural with a singular
meaning.</def> <rj><au>Gower.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wits take <qex>lodgings</qex> in the sound of Bow.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Abiding place; harbor; cover.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fair bosom . . . the <qex>lodging</qex> of delight.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lodging house</b></col>, <cd>a house where lodgings are
provided and let.</cd> -- <col><b>Lodging room</b></col>, <cd>a room in
which a person lodges, esp. a hired room.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lodgings</ent>⟦br⟧
